# Windows batch files are parsed by cmd.exe, which REQUIRES CRLF line endings.
# With LF-only endings cmd.exe loses line-sync on goto/call/( ) blocks and starts
# executing comment (REM) text as commands. Force CRLF so a checkout on any
# platform (and any core.autocrlf setting) always produces a runnable script.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
